<br>
Tell you the truth, mages are even more utility than wizards. You are NEEDED for resist summoned gear, mod rods, eb stones, CoH, and other things. People NEED you. And while all that's going on, you can still be more useful by tossing your epic pet on some mob they happen to be fighting, if they let you have your pet up at the time. The problem is that due to pathing and other responsibilities mages can lose their pets and cause problems, so often they're just told not to have them up at all. That's when you're rendered into a second rate nuker and summoning bitch.<br>
<br>
You have to look at what the true roll of a class is. The TRUE roll of a wizard is master of direct and ae spell damage, and teleportation mastery. The TRUE roll of a magician is a master of summoning, while taking an important roll in nuking and debuffing. Magicans summon everthing from mod rods to pets to people themselves. If Magicians were to match wizards in nuke ability, that would be unbalanced because of your pet... converting wizards into petless mages that can port. Wizards and mages are very close in some respects, but very very different and balanced in their own ways. Just remember, for pure battle damage, the only classes that are soley meant to do battle damage are wizards and rogues... that's their purpose. The rest either are pullers, tankers, debuffers, healers, supporters, or some combination of those. <p><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=400>
